childMdx.excerpt: A bird sings alone its sunset song, the only sound ever made:   worship.   Praise for One from this single starling stirred by sea breeze…
There is only one light passing through two, interfering with itself to paint a pattern on the screen of  you .   Gradually the gaps grow…
The moon has moved since I first arrived here: now the light breaks in unfettered by my balcony bars; pure and still as I breathe out and…
